{
  "texts": [
    "Thus, we have shown that h p (h(y ′) ∧ x) = y ′, so setting y = h(y ′) ∧ x completes the proof of p-⊑-back.For R-forth, if xR i y, then y ⊑ f i (x) by Lemma 5.15, so h p (y)⊑ ′ h p (f i (x)) by (a), so h p (y) ⊑ ′ f ′ i (h p (x)) by (e), so h p (x)R ′ i h p (y) by Lemma 5.15.",
    "For p-R-back, suppose h p (x)R ′ i y ′.",
    "First we claim f i (x)∧h(y ′) ̸ = ⊥.",
    "If not, then f i (x) ⊑ -h(y ′), which by adjointness implies x ⊑ ■ i -h(y ′) and hence x ⊑ h(■ ′ i -y ′), which by (a) and (b) implies h p (x) ⊑ h p (h(■ ′ i -y ′)) ⊑ ■ ′ i -y ′, which contradicts h p (x)R ′ i y ′.",
    "Second, we claim that y ′ ⊑ h p (f i (x) ∧ h(y ′))."
  ]
}